  "prompt": "Why isn't the state Odisha highlighted in the national media as other states?",
  "response": "Odisha (formerly Orissa) receives less national media attention due to several factors:\n\n1. Limited economic and political influence\n- Relatively smaller population\n- Lower economic output compared to larger states\n- Less representation in national political parties\n\n2. Geographic location\n- Located in eastern India\n- Less strategically prominent compared to western or northern states\n\n3. Lower urbanization and industrial development\n- Predominantly rural economy\n- Limited major industrial centers\n- Fewer metropolitan cities\n\n4. Media bias\n- Mainstream media often focuses on larger, more economically significant states\n- Less representation of regional issues and achievements\n\n5. Limited communication infrastructure\n- Historically weaker media ecosystem\n- Fewer local media outlets with national reach\n\n6. Cultural representation\n- Less visibility in national cultural narratives\n- Limited representation in national entertainment platforms\n\nHowever, Odisha does have significant strengths:\n- Rich cultural heritage\n- Diverse tribal populations\n- Advanced disaster management capabilities\n- Emerging industrial potential\n- Significant contributions in art, literature, and sports\n\nIn recent years, the state has been gaining more recognition through improved infrastructure, tourism, and economic development initiatives.",
